.agents/skills/netscript-deno-toolchain/SKILL.md:description: The Deno 2.8 native dependency, release, and inspection toolchain (deno outdated/update/why/info/add/remove/audit/ci/bump-version/publish/pack/doc, catalogs, isolatedDeclarations). Use BEFORE hand-rolling dependency bumps, version checks, registry curls, publish scripting, or doc generation in the NetScript workspace — these built-ins replace most ad hoc tooling and the per-dep curl loops that burn tokens. Pairs with the .llm/tools/deps toolbelt and the netscript-tools skill.
.agents/skills/netscript-deno-toolchain/SKILL.md:| `deno update [<pkg>] [--latest]` | rewrite specifiers to newer versions | prefer manual catalog edits for review; see Catalogs |
.agents/skills/netscript-deno-toolchain/SKILL.md:- A root `deno.json` `catalog` block centralizes versions; members reference `"<pkg>": "catalog:"`.
.agents/skills/netscript-deno-toolchain/SKILL.md:- **`catalog:` is npm-only.** `npm:<pkg>@catalog:` works; bare `"<pkg>": "catalog:"` works for npm.
.agents/skills/netscript-deno-toolchain/SKILL.md:- **JSR deps cannot use catalog.** `jsr:pkg@catalog:` is rejected (`Invalid package specifier`) and a
.agents/skills/netscript-deno-toolchain/SKILL.md:  `jsr:`-valued catalog entry warns `Invalid version requirement`. Keep JSR deps as inline `jsr:`
.agents/skills/netscript-deno-toolchain/SKILL.md:- `publish:dry-run` materializes `catalog:` → `npm:<pkg>@<version>` per member before dry-run; mirror
.agents/skills/netscript-deno-toolchain/SKILL.md:| `deno publish [--dry-run] [--allow-dirty] [--allow-slow-types]` | publish to JSR; auto-rewrites workspace specifiers. Repo uses `deno task publish:dry-run` (per-member, catalog-materialized) |
